This peptide is said to correspond to residues 217-225 of the Nucleoprotein from Influenza A/Japan/305, but the corresponding sequence found in that protein has a I residue at position 225 instead of a T. It is predicted to bind HLA-B14 molecules based on the presence of 3 out of 5 conserved anchor residues for that MHC allele. An internal database source is provided here to account for the lack of agreement between the NP sequences present in the current protein databases and the author provided sequence.
